// Context  
In the context of Linked Data, there are two query paradigms for requesting decentralized knowledge graphs: Federated Queries and Link Traversal Query Processing (LTQP). While multiple similarities exist between these paradigms, no comparative study exists in the literature.
// Need
Federated queries, despite remaining challenges, represent a well-studied topic, whereas LTQP optimization techniques are in their infancy. This limited understanding of LTQP results in practically slow queries that lack sophisticated query planning methods beyond simple heuristics.
// Task
To mature this query paradigm, it is essential to develop query planning techniques that improve query processing time.
// Object
In this paper, we propose formalizing LTQP as a variant of federated querying to leverage established strategies from the federated query domain. Through this formalization, we adapt the FedUp algorithm for LTQP using a summary method called the _Shape Index_ and implement this approach in the Comunica query engine. We benchmark our approach and evaluate multiple query processing metrics to assess its effectiveness.

